author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm extension --install pm-<alias> and @unbrained/pm-<alias> resolve to the bundled catalog or fail with a suggestion listing catalog aliases; never-block recovery bundle included.
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox audit #3: `pm extension install pm-beads` (also @unbrained/pm-beads) falls through to local-path resolution and errors 'Local extension source does not exist: .../pm-beads'. The bundled catalog alias is 'beads' (install_command `pm install beads --project`). Agents naturally try the package folder name or npm name first — never-block demands a mapping, not a dead end.\n\n## Approach\nBefore the local-path fallback in the extension install resolver, match the target against: bundled catalog aliases, package folder names (pm-<alias>), and npm names (@unbrained/pm-<alias>). Exact match → install the catalog alias directly (or emit the exact install command); near-miss → did-you-mean via the existing OSA Damerau suggester.\n\n## Definition of done\nAll three spellings of every bundled package either install or emit the exact catalog command; unknown names still reach the local-path error; spec covers alias, folder-name, npm-name, and near-miss paths."
